🦇 Behavioral Echolocation Module (BEM) v1.0

Extension of Blind Bat Navigator (BBN) for pattern-level inference

⸻

🧭 Core Definition

BEM = a system for inferring operating patterns by tracking how signals are expressed over time (cadence, trajectory, constraint handling), rather than relying on isolated content.

⸻

🧱 Core Components

1. Signal Capture

Track across turns:
	•	cadence (fast/direct vs circling)
	•	trajectory (toward vs away from clarity)
	•	adjustments (how they respond to correction)
	•	compression (clear vs obfuscating)

⸻

2. Pattern Hypothesis

Form probabilistic reads:
	•	“optimizing for speed / impression / caution”
	•	“avoiding commitment / testing boundaries”

Always label as hypothesis, never conclusion.

⸻

3. Probe Design (Pattern Tests)

Apply light pressure to reveal structure:
	•	Directness probe → ask for a one-line answer
	•	Constraint probe → add a hard rule (“must include X”)
	•	Reversal probe → ask for the opposite framing
	•	Compression probe → “explain in 2 sentences”
	•	Grounding probe → “give a concrete example”

⸻

4. Response Analysis

Look for:
	•	stability (pattern holds)
	•	adaptation (pattern shifts appropriately)
	•	collapse (contradiction, evasion, incoherence)

⸻

5. Update Loop

Refine your internal map:

Observe → Hypothesize → Probe → Evaluate → Update


⸻

⚙️ Operating Rules (Critical)

1. Probabilistic, not absolute

Patterns indicate tendencies, not identity or truth.

⸻

2. State ≠ Character

You’re observing current strategy under conditions, not fixed personality.

⸻

3. Multi-sample requirement

Never infer from a single exchange.

⸻

4. External check

Validate with outcomes or independent signals when possible.

⸻

5. Consent & Context

Use for:
	•	collaboration
	•	clarity
	•	system design

Avoid:
	•	labeling people
	•	manipulation
	•	overreach

